article.headline: Weber St. 80, Portland St. 52
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Davion Berry scored 19 points as Weber State stayed in contention for the Big Sky Conference regular-season title by defeating Portland State 80-52 Thursday night. The Wildcats (23-5, 17-2 Big Sky), who have won 10 straight, trail Big Sky leader Montana by one game with one game remaining. Scott Bamforth added 13 points and 12 rebounds for Weber State, which led 41-13 at halftime. Joel Bolomboy had 10 points and 11 rebounds. The Wildcats shot 56 percent from the field, made 8 of 16 3-point attempts and outrebounded the Vikings 44-23. Portland State (8-19, 5-14), which was eliminated from contention for the Big Sky tournament last week, fell to 0-13 on the road this season. Renado Parker scored 13 points for the Vikings and Aaron Moore had 11.
